Class SmartObjectMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fasterxml.jackson.core.TreeCodec
      • com.fasterxml.jackson.core.ObjectCodec
        • com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper
          • craterdog.smart.SmartObjectMapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.fasterxml.jackson.core.Versioned, Serializable

    public class SmartObjectMapper
extends com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper
    This object mapper handles the conversion of a smart object to and from a JSON string. The mapper can be configured to censor sensitive attributes that are marked with the @Sensitive annotation.
    Author:
    Jeff Webb, Mukesh Jyothi, Derk Norton
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • _defaultPrettyPrinter

        protected com.fasterxml.jackson.core.PrettyPrinter _defaultPrettyPrinter()
        This method overrides the same method in the super class and returns a better pretty printer implementation. NOTE: This looks like it would set the default pretty printer for all uses by the object mapper but it does NOT. I think this is a case of the original intent changing or being lost over time. There is an enhancement request to address this problem, for more details see: https://github.com/FasterXML/jackson-databind/issues/689.
        Overrides:
        _defaultPrettyPrinter in class com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.ObjectMapper
        Returns:
        The better pretty printer to be used to format the JSON output.

        Returns:
        The better pretty printer to be used to format the JSON output.
